LORD ELDER nodded, "Of course, of course, and that is probrably the
only reason why this alliance still stands, because they need each
other."  ELDER shook his head, "But I have the feeling that this will
end badly."

ELDER paused thoughtfully as he looked up at the screen, "But how can
be we seeing Cheetor's entry code in the computer." ELDER said.

"Insufficient data." LEGACY said coldly. "At the moment the most
likely convergence of events would be that he is the originator of the
attempts to access the satellite." LEGACY paused, "However that would
not fit well with his known personality profile."

There was a nod from ELDER, "You're right, this is not like Cheetor at
all. He would never had done anything like this."

LEGACY turned to regard LORD ELDER, "Without additional data it is
impossible to know for a reasonable amount of certainty the who the
true author is of these entries. It could have been Cheetor, or an
individual who knows his entry codes."

ELDER nodded, he knew that LEGACY rarely guessed until he was nearly
sure of the answer. "We need to find more answers." ELDER said.

"On that we agree." LEGACY said as he returned his attention to the
image on the screen.

ELDER turned to look at WINDLORD and PERCEPTOR, "Any suggestions?"

(TAG)

- Preston
